# Trivy vulnerability suppressions for SPARC
# ============================================================================
# Each suppressed CVE includes classification, justification, mitigating
# controls, and reference links. Review and re-evaluate on each major release.
#
# Classifications:
#   DISPUTED    — Upstream maintainers or NVD dispute the vulnerability
#   MITIGATED   — Real vulnerability but fully mitigated by SPARC's deployment
#   FALSE POSITIVE — Not a vulnerability; expected behavior or wrong context
# ============================================================================

# DS-0002 — Trivy filesystem misconfiguration: image runs as root
# Classification: FALSE POSITIVE for production
# Description: Trivy fs scan reports DS-0002 against tests/api/Dockerfile,
#   the dev/CI test-runner image used to execute the Python pytest suite
#   against a deployed SPARC instance. tests/api/Dockerfile is NOT the
#   production image — it's CI tooling that runs ephemerally in GitHub
#   Actions. The production Dockerfile (./Dockerfile, Red Hat UBI9 minimal
#   base since #742/v1.12.0) already runs as non-root UID 1000 and is
#   properly hardened.
# Mitigation: dev/test image isolation; never deployed to production.
#   Reviewed annually as part of test-tooling audit.
# Reference: trivy-fs scan run 25409853872 against tests/api/Dockerfile
# Reviewed: 2026-07-20
DS-0002
